    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan telegraphs that the English, German, and French ministers have given
                        an undertaking, which the Chilean Government requires as a condition of
                        clearing cargoes from Chilean ports, that if ships should be forcibly
                        compelled to enter ports in control of revolutionists their liberation will
                        be exacted by the fleets of their respective nations. Mr. Egan asks whether
                        he may give the same assurance.</p>
            </div>
